issue_body:
[ValidateSimpleDate](https://github.com/moov-io/ach/blob/master/validators.go#L136-L151) seems to have a lot of logic that could be simplified by using the `time` package. This would also solve the TODO of validating during a leap year. 

here is a possible implementation:

```Go
// validateSimpleDate will return the incoming string only if it matches a valid YYMMDD
// date format. (Y=Year, M=Month, D=Day)
func (v *validator) validateSimpleDate(s string) string {
	//YYMMDD
	layout := "060102"

	_, err := time.Parse(layout, s)
	if err != nil {
		return ""
	}
	return s
}
```

